\begin{abstract}
We present \dataset, a multimodal benchmark linking Twitter/X posts
to Polymarket prediction market dynamics.
Each instance pairs a social post (text and optional image/OCR)
with a market question, its formal resolution rule, sibling-market
context, and a live price--volume time series.
The benchmark is organized around two complementary objectives.
\emph{Forecast tasks} ask whether a post signals future market
movement; their labels derive from tick data that postdates the post
and are computed via deterministic SQL at zero annotation cost.
\emph{Resolution tasks} ask how a post serves as formal evidence;
their labels require human judgment over market rules and post
content.
This design yields a structural anti-contamination guarantee that
existing financial benchmarks lack: no retrieval shortcut or LLM
pretraining leakage can inflate scores.
Baseline experiments confirm that the forecast tasks remain
substantially open for state-of-the-art vision--language models. The benchmark can be accessed from \textcolor{blue}{\url{https://github.com/mlsys-io/EventXBench}}.
\end{abstract}
  
 
