\subsection{Resolution Tasks}
 
\smallskip\noindent\textbf{T2 --- Post-to-Market Linking.}
Given a post $p$ and a candidate set $\mathcal{C}(p)$ recalled by
BGE-large-en-v1.5~\cite{xiao2023cpack} / FAISS~\cite{johnson2021faiss}
dense retrieval, the model must identify
the single market $m^*$ that $p$ most specifically addresses, or
output \texttt{none}.
Surface entity overlap alone is insufficient: a post about a
politician's health may match markets on election outcome,
resignation probability, and policy votes simultaneously.
Metrics: Accuracy@1, MRR, \texttt{none}-class $F_1$.
 
\smallskip\noindent\textbf{T3 --- Evidence Grading and Resolution Potential.}
Given a post linked to market $m$, the model assigns an ordered
evidence grade (Table~\ref{tab:grades}): grade~5 means the post
alone satisfies all formal resolution conditions (source, predicate,
timing, threshold); lower grades capture indirect, speculative, or
off-topic signal.
Metrics: quadratic-weighted $\kappa$, \texttt{resolving}-class
precision, macro-$F_1$.
 
