\subsection{Annotation}
\label{sec:annotation}
 
Both resolution tasks store the silver label, LLM output, human
correction, and annotator ID for audit.
All forecast task labels are computed deterministically from the tick
database via SQL; reliability is cross-validated against two
independent price providers (mean absolute price deviation:
\textbf{[mad]\%}).
 
\smallskip\noindent\emph{T2 annotation.}
The three-way classification pipeline (Qwen2.5-4B with human review
of \texttt{REVIEW} cases) is described in \S\ref{sec:dataset};
accepted links are stored in \texttt{tweet\_market\_link}.
 
\smallskip\noindent\emph{T3 annotation.}
The pipeline operates in four stages.
\textit{(1)~Rule parsing.} GPT-4o~\cite{openai2023gpt4} parses each
market's resolution rule once into a structured predicate object
(source whitelist, predicate string, deadline, numeric threshold);
the object is human-verified and cached in Postgres.
\textit{(2)~Deterministic pre-checks.} Four SQL/NLP checks ---
source authority, time condition, threshold, and predicate entity
match (spaCy + fuzzy) --- each return
\texttt{pass}/\texttt{fail}/\texttt{uncertain}.
All four \texttt{pass} $\Rightarrow$ candidate grade~5; source
\texttt{fail} caps the grade at $\leq 3$.
\textit{(3)~Conditional LLM.} Invoked only when any check returns
\texttt{uncertain}; the model outputs a grade, confidence score, and
four ambiguity flags (conditional, sarcasm, source unclear, threshold
ambiguous).
\textit{(4)~Auto-accept / human route.} Silver labels are accepted
if all pre-checks \texttt{pass}, grade $\leq 1$, confidence
$\geq 0.90$, and no flags are set; otherwise, the instance is routed
to a human annotator (grade $\geq 3$, any flag, or confidence
$< 0.70$).
Of the 342,552 annotated instances, the grade distribution is:
grade~3 \texttt{indirect\_report} (61.9\%),
grade~2 \texttt{speculation} (26.3\%),
grade~1 \texttt{commentary} (5.6\%),
grade~0 \texttt{noise} (4.4\%),
grade~4 \texttt{strong\_direct} (1.2\%), and
grade~5 \texttt{resolving} (0.6\%).
The LLM was invoked for 74,529 instances (21.8\%) where at least one
pre-check was uncertain; 9,464 (2.8\%) were auto-accepted as silver
labels, and 65,065 (19.0\%) received human review.
 
