% ============================================================
\subsection{Benchmark Setup}
 
\smallskip\noindent\textbf{Data splits} are temporal by market
creation date (train: 2021--2024 / val: Jan--Jun~2025 /
test: Jul~2025--Feb~2026) to prevent leakage.
Test and validation instances are fully resolved; all resolution-task
test/val labels are human-verified (no silver).
Table~\ref{tab:t4stats} reports the \taskname{T4} label distribution
across the 4,803 valid instances.
The majority (58.7\%) exhibit flat or small movement, consistent
with most posts being informative but not price-moving.
Of 1,983 non-flat instances, 645 are confounded (32.5\%,
higher than the 20.1\% overall rate), leaving {1,338} clean
directional instances eligible for \taskname{T5}.
407 have complete T5 labels (268 non-confounded).
Confounded instances are excluded from test and retained in
training with a flag.
 
\smallskip\noindent\textbf{Metrics.}
Each task uses metrics suited to its output type.
\taskname{T2}: Accuracy@1, MRR, and \texttt{none}-class $F_1$.
\taskname{T3}: quadratic-weighted $\kappa$, \texttt{resolving}-class
precision, and macro-$F_1$.
\taskname{T1}: macro-$F_1$ and \texttt{high}-class precision@$K$.
\taskname{T4}: direction accuracy, magnitude macro-$F_1$, and
Spearman~$\rho$ on the continuous horizon curve.
\taskname{T6}: macro-$F_1$ and mean absolute error (MAE) on onset lag
in minutes.
\taskname{T5}: Spearman~$\rho$ for the two continuous targets and
\texttt{decay\_class} macro-$F_1$.
All classification metrics are macro-averaged to penalize poor
minority-class performance.
LLM baselines are run three times with different random seeds;
we report the mean and include 95\% bootstrap confidence intervals
in the supplementary material.

