\subsection{Analysis}
\label{sec:analysis}
 
We conduct four targeted analyses to surface insights unique to
\dataset's structure.
 
% --- Anti-contamination ---
\smallskip\noindent\textbf{Anti-contamination validation.}
We probe whether LLM pretraining leaks Polymarket outcomes by asking
GPT-4o to predict each market's resolution \emph{without} any post
--- only the market question and creation date.
On training-split markets (pre-2025), GPT-4o achieves [.]\% accuracy,
meaningfully above the 25.7\% YES base rate, consistent with outcome
memorization from pretraining corpora.
On test-split markets (post-Jul~2025), accuracy drops to [.]\%,
indistinguishable from the base rate
($p = $ [.], binomial test).
This confirms that \dataset's temporal split renders forecast labels
immune to pretraining leakage --- a guarantee that existing financial
benchmarks, whose labels are derived from historical prices already
present in LLM training data, cannot provide.
 
